@startuml JWT-Validierung-Gateway
title Sequenzdiagramm: JWT-Validierung im Gateway

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2

actor "Client" as Client
participant "Gateway\n(8080)" as Gateway
participant "Backend-Service" as Backend

== Geschützter Endpunkt ==

Client -> Gateway: GET /api/users\nAuthorization: Bearer <JWT>
activate Gateway

Gateway -> Gateway: JwtClaimsExtractionFilter

alt Kein Authorization Header
    Gateway --> Client: 401 Unauthorized\n{"error": "Missing Authorization header"}
else Ungültiger Token
    Gateway -> Gateway: JWT parsen & validieren
    Gateway --> Client: 401 Unauthorized\n{"error": "Invalid JWT token"}
else Token abgelaufen
    Gateway -> Gateway: Ablaufzeit prüfen
    Gateway --> Client: 401 Unauthorized\n{"error": "JWT token has expired"}
else Token gültig
    Gateway -> Gateway: Claims extrahieren:\n- sub → X-User-Id\n- email → X-User-Email\n- role → X-User-Roles\n- tenant_ids → X-User-Tenant-Ids\n- matrikelnummer → X-User-Matrikelnummer
    
    Gateway -> Backend: Request + X-User-* Headers
    activate Backend
    Backend -> Backend: Autorisierung anhand\nder X-User-* Headers
    Backend --> Gateway: Response
    deactivate Backend
    
    Gateway --> Client: Response
end

deactivate Gateway

== Öffentlicher Endpunkt (Login) ==

Client -> Gateway: POST /api/auth/login\n{email, password}
activate Gateway
note right of Gateway: Kein JWT erforderlich\n(shouldNotFilter = true)
Gateway -> Backend: Weiterleitung ohne JWT-Prüfung
activate Backend
Backend --> Gateway: {token: "..."}
deactivate Backend
Gateway --> Client: {token: "..."}
deactivate Gateway

@enduml
